 TASKS

 Connectivity between four routers has been established. IP connectivity must be configured in the order presented to complete the implementation.

No dynamic routing protocols are included.

1. Configure static routing using host routes to establish connectivity from router R3 to the router R1 Loopback address using the source IP of 209.165.200.230.

2. Configure an IPv4 default route on router R2 destined for router R4.

3. Configure an IPv6 default router on router R2 destined for router R4.


SOLUTION

1. Configure static routing using host routes to establish connectivity from router R3 to the router R1 Loopback address using the source IP of 209.165.200.230.

Take note of the word 'host routes'

When we say host route it simply means a route to a single, specific IP address (a host).

A host route uses a /32 subnet mask for the given IP.


Since we are configuring a static route, we have to configure all the necessary routes in order for R3 to ping R1's loopback IP.

> For R3 to reach R1's loopback, it will need to send its packet to the IP of R2's e0/1 interface as its next-hop

@R3
conf t
 ip route 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.255 209.165.200.229
 end
This static route simply says:

If R3 needs to send a packet to R1's loopback interface, it will need to send it to R2's e0/1 interface that has the IP of 209.165.200.228


Then we need to make sure R1 can reply to R3

@R1
conf t
 ip route 209.165.200.228 255.255.255.252 209.165.200.226
 end
Finally, we need to make sure the next hop of both R1 and R3, which is R2, also knows how to get to the loopback of R1.

@R2
conf t
 ip route 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.255 209.165.200.225
 end
Verify: From R3, send a ping to R1's loopback 1 interface

@R3
ping 192.168.1.1


2. Configure an IPv4 default route on router R2 destined for router R4.

@R2
conf t
 ip route 0.0.0.0 0.0.0.0 209.165.202.130
 end


3. Configure an IPv6 default route on router R2 destined for router R4

IPv6 static/default route configuration is similar to IPv4.

ipv6 route [Destination/Prefix] [Next hop/interface]

@R2
conf t
 ipv6 route ::/0 2001:db8:abcd::2
 end

